  "text": "Conventional MRI is a very useful tool for the detection of brain metastases but cannot readily differentiate between tumor histologies. Brain metastases are typically nodular, iso-or hypointense on T1-weighted imaging, hyperintense on T2-weighted imaging, and avidly enhance after contrast administration regardless of their primary site of origin [CITATION_1] . Even the presence of hemorrhage which ",
